sudo : executes a command with superuser privileges
ls :  directory listing
ls -la : list files with details
grep pattern file : searches for a specific pattern within a file
mv myfile.txt /home/user/Documents/ : Move a file to another directory
mv old_filename new_filename : Renaming a file only.
cp source_file target_file : This copies the entire file (not just the content) 
cat source_file > target_file : This overwrites the target_file with the content of source_file
cat source_file >> target_file : To append the content instead of overwriting
mkdir yogesh : creates a directory yogesh 
cd yogesh : change directory to yogesh
cd : change to home directory
pwd : shows current working directory
cat file_name : displays the content of the file
touch file_name : create or update a file

